WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:05.797
[Darlene Love's "Christmas
(Baby, Please Come Home)"]

00:05.839 --> 00:11.761
♪ ♪

00:11.803 --> 00:14.889
[buzzing]

00:16.850 --> 00:18.101
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:18.143 --> 00:20.478
- ♪ The snow's coming down ♪

00:20.520 --> 00:21.855
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:21.896 --> 00:24.399
- ♪ I'm watching it fall ♪

00:24.441 --> 00:25.692
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:25.734 --> 00:28.236
- ♪ Lots of people around ♪

00:28.278 --> 00:29.529
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:29.571 --> 00:31.865
- ♪ Baby, please come home ♪

00:31.906 --> 00:33.199
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:33.241 --> 00:35.785
- ♪ The church bells in town ♪

00:35.827 --> 00:37.037
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:37.078 --> 00:39.372
- ♪ Are ringing in song ♪

00:39.414 --> 00:40.623
- ♪ Christmas ♪

00:40.665 --> 00:43.084
- ♪ Full of happy sounds ♪

00:43.126 --> 00:46.296
- ♪ Christmas ♪
- ♪ Baby, please come home ♪

00:46.337 --> 00:50.258
- Hey, Johnny, what are you
doing down here?

00:52.469 --> 00:54.971
- Well, we finally get
everybody back together

00:55.013 --> 00:58.183
to take on the ISA and...

00:58.224 --> 01:00.602
they bench me.

01:00.643 --> 01:03.354
- Yeah, well, Starman asked me
to stay behind, too,

01:03.396 --> 01:06.357
to get the Rocket Racer
ready just--just in case.

01:06.399 --> 01:08.109
- Life on the bench.

01:08.151 --> 01:10.236
Doesn't feel good, does it,
Stripesy?

01:10.278 --> 01:12.655
- Speaking honestly, it can be
a little rough on the old ego,

01:12.697 --> 01:15.575
but I trust whatever Sylvester
thinks is best.

01:15.617 --> 01:17.744
- Spoken like a loyal sidekick.

01:17.786 --> 01:20.288
- Hey, nothing wrong
with being a sidekick.

01:20.330 --> 01:21.581
- Yeah, but see,
that's the thing.

01:21.623 --> 01:23.124
I'm not even that.

01:23.166 --> 01:26.211
I'm the JSA charity case.

01:26.252 --> 01:28.171
Heck, Pat, on paper,

01:28.213 --> 01:31.299
Thunderbolt is more powerful
than Green Lantern,

01:31.341 --> 01:34.052
Flash, all of 'em combined,

01:34.094 --> 01:36.221
but in my hands,

01:36.262 --> 01:39.349
it's nothing but another mess
for the JSA to clean up.

01:39.390 --> 01:44.020
- ♪ 'Cause I remember
when you were here ♪

01:44.062 --> 01:45.647
♪ And all the fun we had ♪

01:45.688 --> 01:49.150
- Oh, hey,
how's a little eggnog sound?

01:49.192 --> 01:51.152
It's my dad's old recipe.

01:51.194 --> 01:52.445
It's got a little kick too.
[elevator dings]

01:52.487 --> 01:55.115
- Ooh, I like a kick!

01:56.741 --> 01:58.159
- They got Solomon Grundy.

01:58.201 --> 01:59.828
- What?

01:59.869 --> 02:01.412
You need backup? You got 'em.

02:01.454 --> 02:03.873
- Sorry, Pat. Just Johnny.

02:03.915 --> 02:05.500
- But, Wildcat,
I mean, you know,

02:05.542 --> 02:08.378
we're talking about
the entire ISA now, right?

02:08.419 --> 02:10.213
- Members only.
Sylvester insisted.

02:10.255 --> 02:12.966
[dramatic music]

02:13.007 --> 02:14.300
Hey!

02:14.342 --> 02:16.302
You got a kid to look out for.

02:16.344 --> 02:18.429
There's nothing more important.

02:18.471 --> 02:19.514
Let's go.

02:19.556 --> 02:24.644
♪ ♪

02:24.686 --> 02:25.895
- Okay, good luck.

02:25.937 --> 02:29.023
- Thanks, Stripesy.

02:29.065 --> 02:32.235
Hey, when I get back
we'll have that eggnog, okay?

02:32.277 --> 02:34.112
♪ ♪

02:34.154 --> 02:35.947
♪ ♪

02:35.989 --> 02:38.283
- ♪ Oh, please ♪

02:38.324 --> 02:40.201
- ♪ Christmas ♪

02:40.243 --> 02:43.663
- ♪ Oh, please ♪

02:45.874 --> 02:48.835
[exciting music]

02:48.877 --> 02:54.174
♪ ♪

02:56.134 --> 02:59.095
[light instrumental music]

02:59.137 --> 03:06.227
♪ ♪

03:25.330 --> 03:27.165
- Hey, boys, it's Dugan.
There he is.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.042
- Hey!
Oh, Dugan!

03:29.083 --> 03:30.210
- Morning, Dugan.

03:30.251 --> 03:32.212
- Devin, Lutz, Marky,

03:32.253 --> 03:33.922
it's a little early,
don't you think?

03:33.963 --> 03:35.590
Did you set your alarm
just to bully me?

03:35.632 --> 03:37.425
- To get paid, paperboy.

03:37.467 --> 03:39.719
- Ah, why do you need
the money, a brain transplant?

03:39.761 --> 03:41.512
- All right, that's gonna
cost you extra, Dugan.

03:41.554 --> 03:42.889
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

03:45.850 --> 03:47.268
- Get 'em while it's hot!

03:47.310 --> 03:49.229
- Ooh!
- You look great.

03:49.270 --> 03:50.980
- Thank you!
- Ahh, I just love

03:51.022 --> 03:53.233
the smell of bacon
in the morning, don't you?

03:53.274 --> 03:55.235
Smells like...
[sniffs]

03:55.276 --> 03:56.611
Victory!

03:56.653 --> 03:58.112
- Yeah, see, never count
your winnings

03:58.154 --> 04:00.031
before you collect,
okay, Court?

04:00.073 --> 04:02.909
- The Shade has no idea
who he's up against.

04:02.951 --> 04:05.536
- First of all, he's obviously
very dangerous.

04:05.578 --> 04:07.580
So I think you should
definitely bring S.T.R.I.P.E.

04:07.622 --> 04:10.166
- Mom, we need
the element of surprise.

04:10.208 --> 04:11.668
S.T.R.I.P.E.'s as subtle
as a tank.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.795
- Doesn't he have, like,
a silent mode?

04:13.836 --> 04:17.090
- That's a good idea.
- Silent mode? Seriously?

04:17.131 --> 04:19.342
- Or--I don't know--
invisibility?

04:19.384 --> 04:22.428
- Ugh, Mom, you're--
you're embarrassing yourself.

04:22.470 --> 04:24.347
Let the professionals
figure it out.

04:24.389 --> 04:26.057
- Okay, listen,
here's the deal.

04:26.099 --> 04:27.767
No one's gonna make a move

04:27.809 --> 04:30.270
until we have a plan that
everyone agrees with, okay?

04:30.311 --> 04:33.022
- Okay.
- Hey, you doing JSA stuff?

04:33.064 --> 04:34.274
- [clears throat]

04:34.315 --> 04:36.484
- Yup.
- Ah, The Shade?

04:36.526 --> 04:37.819
Who's this creep?

04:37.860 --> 04:38.820
- Somebody's butt
we're gonna kick--

04:38.861 --> 04:40.238
- Carefully.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.782
We're gonna do it
very, very carefully,

04:42.824 --> 04:46.494
and it's not something you need
to be worrying about, Mike.

04:46.536 --> 04:48.788
- Yeah.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.540
Yeah, whatever.

04:50.581 --> 04:53.293
- Okay, Barb,
what can I get you?

04:53.334 --> 04:56.379
- Toast and jam.
- Toast and jam.

04:56.421 --> 04:58.131
Court, what would you like?

05:01.217 --> 05:03.052
- What?
- [speaking indistinctly]

05:03.094 --> 05:06.139
- I'm on my route right now.
Don't you hear the dog?

05:08.016 --> 05:10.893
Okay, okay.
Another customer?

05:10.935 --> 05:13.438
I got plenty, Mr. Bloomkiss.
Please just give it to Jakeem.

05:13.479 --> 05:16.024
It'll be in better hands.

05:16.065 --> 05:18.234
Okay. Okay, okay, fine, fine.

05:18.276 --> 05:19.944
I'll take it.

05:19.986 --> 05:22.655
What was it again?

05:22.697 --> 05:24.198
210...

05:24.240 --> 05:26.200
[shimmering tone]

05:27.744 --> 05:29.078
Come on.

05:29.120 --> 05:32.332
[suspenseful music]

05:32.373 --> 05:35.335
- [speaking indistinctly]

05:35.376 --> 05:36.961
- Yeah, yeah, I got it.

05:37.003 --> 05:39.047
Yeah, thanks. [sighs]

05:39.088 --> 05:41.424
- [speaking indistinctly]

05:41.466 --> 05:47.889
♪ ♪

05:53.061 --> 05:55.772
- Paperboy
and human punching bag.

05:59.067 --> 06:00.777
Wish I was a superhero.

06:02.195 --> 06:06.616
♪ ♪

06:06.657 --> 06:08.701
- [indistinct shout]

06:08.743 --> 06:15.833
♪ ♪

06:29.680 --> 06:32.809
- What the heck?

06:32.850 --> 06:34.143
Oh, shoot!

06:34.185 --> 06:41.275
♪ ♪

06:51.452 --> 06:53.037
"So cool"?

06:53.079 --> 06:56.374
Ah.
- Whoo-whee!

06:56.416 --> 06:58.709
[zapping]

06:58.751 --> 07:00.044
- Ah!

07:00.086 --> 07:01.754
- Whoo-ooh!

07:01.796 --> 07:03.506
[laughing] Oh, yeah!

07:03.548 --> 07:05.299
- What the heck are you?

07:05.341 --> 07:08.553
- I'm your new best friend
and you don't even know it!

07:08.594 --> 07:10.763
[laughs]

07:15.476 --> 07:16.811
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- What's going on?

07:16.853 --> 07:19.063
- What's going on
is that you, Mike Dugan,

07:19.105 --> 07:21.774
are now in control of me,

07:21.816 --> 07:23.985
The Thunderbolt!
[thunder booming]

07:24.026 --> 07:25.611
- The Thunderbolt?

07:25.653 --> 07:28.489
- As in Johnny Thunder
and The Thunderbolt!

07:28.531 --> 07:31.075
Of the Justice Society
of America!

07:31.117 --> 07:32.285
You're so lucky.

07:32.326 --> 07:34.120
- This belonged to the JSA?

07:34.162 --> 07:35.496
- Yep! You said the magic word,

07:35.538 --> 07:37.623
and now I'm back in action.

07:37.665 --> 07:39.375
- Wait, so the magic words
are "so cool"?

07:39.417 --> 07:41.711
- Word, singular.

07:41.752 --> 07:44.046
It's pronounced "sowkewl"

07:44.088 --> 07:47.717
in my native homeland
of Bahdnesia.

07:47.758 --> 07:50.470
- Bahd-what?
- It's not on the map anymore.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.637
Thanks for bringing it up.

07:51.679 --> 07:53.306
Sowkewl means "set free

07:53.347 --> 07:56.058
"the all-powerful force
upon the Earth

07:56.100 --> 07:59.896
of the magical
and awe-inspiring Thunderbolt!"

07:59.937 --> 08:02.190
It's also a synonym
for the sound on the chalkboard

08:02.231 --> 08:05.234
that drives everyone crazy,
but I like that sound.

08:05.276 --> 08:06.819
- So if I free the genie--

08:06.861 --> 08:10.615
- Your wish is my command!

08:10.656 --> 08:12.742
- So all the wishes I want?
- Yup!

08:12.783 --> 08:14.076
- Start small.

08:14.118 --> 08:16.621
I'm thirsty.
I wish I had some water.

08:18.164 --> 08:20.917
- [laughs]

08:20.958 --> 08:23.836
- I meant in a glass.

08:23.878 --> 08:27.173
- Rule number one:
you gotta be specific.

08:27.215 --> 08:29.091
Oh, my gosh, you look so silly.

08:29.133 --> 08:31.260
I love it when people do that.

08:31.302 --> 08:33.346
Uh-oh!

08:33.387 --> 08:35.223
Human, three o'clock.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.392
- Morning.
Nothing like a good sweat

08:38.434 --> 08:40.061
to start off the day, huh?

08:40.102 --> 08:42.313
[quirky music]

08:42.355 --> 08:44.273
Wish I was dry.
Did you hear that?

08:44.315 --> 08:47.944
[air whooshing]

08:47.985 --> 08:49.654
Thanks.
- Well, you're welcome.

08:49.695 --> 08:51.864
You're learning.
You're learning.

08:54.200 --> 08:56.744
It's never a good thing
when other people see me.

08:56.786 --> 08:59.914
Reactions range from
mild amusement to sheer panic.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.959
Sent one guy to the ER.
Heart attack, yeah.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.503
He recovered, I think.
I don't know. He was old.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.838
He probably didn't have
much time anyway.

09:07.880 --> 09:11.592
[sighs] This is fun.
So what else can I do for you?

09:11.634 --> 09:14.178
- I'm thinking.

09:14.220 --> 09:15.721
Okay, I got it.

09:15.763 --> 09:17.265
I wish I was taller.

09:17.306 --> 09:20.017
[thunder booming]

09:20.059 --> 09:25.731
♪ ♪

09:25.773 --> 09:27.775
What the hell?
- [laughs]

09:27.817 --> 09:31.070
What? You're taller.
You gotta be--

09:31.112 --> 09:33.573
- Specific. Yeah, okay.

09:33.614 --> 09:34.907
I wish my body was taller.

09:34.949 --> 09:36.492
- Uh-uh, sorry.

09:36.534 --> 09:38.244
Can't wish
for the same thing twice.

09:38.286 --> 09:40.580
And be happy about that
in this case.

09:40.621 --> 09:43.583
Wishes about body
transformation never go well.

09:43.624 --> 09:44.792
- Another rule?

09:44.834 --> 09:47.128
- Well, yeah, there are a few.

09:47.169 --> 09:48.588
Let me see
if I can remember them.

09:48.629 --> 09:50.631
I mean, there are only--

09:50.673 --> 09:52.174
Can't wish
for someone to die.

09:52.216 --> 09:54.427
Can't wish someone back
from the dead.

09:54.468 --> 09:56.137
That's important.
The last guy that tried--

09:56.178 --> 09:57.722
- Okay, back to the point.

09:57.763 --> 10:00.474
So you were a member
of the JSA and so was--

10:00.516 --> 10:03.686
- Johnny Thunder,
my previous master.

10:03.728 --> 10:07.023
And you are my new one.

10:07.064 --> 10:08.858
- Super sowkewl.

10:08.899 --> 10:11.652
[shimmering tone]

10:12.987 --> 10:15.406
- You're late, Rick.

10:17.033 --> 10:21.454
- Sorry, I just had
to feed the dog.

10:21.495 --> 10:23.706
- When'd you get a dog?

10:23.748 --> 10:26.584
- Well, turns out,
the girl who cried wolf

10:26.626 --> 10:28.836
was, uh, right after all.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.421
- Of course I was right.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.256
There's a wolf in Blue Valley.

10:32.298 --> 10:33.716
He's called The Shade,

10:33.758 --> 10:35.718
the last member
of the Injustice Society.

10:35.760 --> 10:38.054
- The Shade worked with the ISA
in the past,

10:38.095 --> 10:39.639
but he quit a while back.

10:39.680 --> 10:41.349
I don't know
what he's up to now,

10:41.390 --> 10:43.976
but he's going by the name
Richard Swift.

10:44.018 --> 10:45.936
He's posing
as an antiques dealer

10:45.978 --> 10:47.938
and he's basically
an antique himself.

10:47.980 --> 10:51.901
There's photographic evidence
of him going back to the 1800s.

10:51.942 --> 10:54.195
- So he's, like, really old?

10:54.236 --> 10:57.073
- Pat thinks he doesn't age.
His powers--

10:57.114 --> 11:00.201
- Are shadows.
His powers are shadows.

11:00.242 --> 11:03.454
He can manipulate them
and travel through darkness.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.623
- So why is he in Blue Valley?

11:05.665 --> 11:07.500
To finish what the ISA started?

11:07.541 --> 11:08.959
- I don't think so, Beth.

11:09.001 --> 11:10.503
He had a falling-out with them

11:10.544 --> 11:13.964
after he helped them
defeat the JSA, but...

11:14.006 --> 11:17.885
I know he's bad news.

11:17.927 --> 11:20.054
I watched him kill
Dr. Mid-Nite.

11:20.096 --> 11:22.056
- Stripesy! Get out!

11:22.098 --> 11:25.226
[screams]

11:25.267 --> 11:27.978
- The Shade killed
Dr. Mid-Nite?

11:28.020 --> 11:31.732
[tense music]

11:31.774 --> 11:34.902
So that means...

11:34.944 --> 11:38.072
Dr. Mid-Nite's
the only one of the JSA

11:38.114 --> 11:41.033
that we haven't
gotten justice for.

11:41.075 --> 11:43.619
We need to.
- First things first,

11:43.661 --> 11:45.454
we need to find out
where The Shade is hiding.

11:45.496 --> 11:46.914
- All for that, but then what?

11:46.956 --> 11:49.041
You can't punch
a shadow, Court.

11:51.168 --> 11:53.087
- Pat?
- Yeah.

11:53.129 --> 11:55.840
- How does one punch a shadow?

11:55.881 --> 11:58.050
- Oh, well, yeah.

11:58.092 --> 12:00.553
I mean, as long
as you're asking,

12:00.594 --> 12:04.598
I did see Starman
incapacitate The Shade one time

12:04.640 --> 12:07.476
using the staff.
- Yes!

12:07.518 --> 12:11.814
- S-so--so we knock out
this shadowy freak.

12:11.856 --> 12:13.899
And then what, Mr. Dugan?

12:16.986 --> 12:19.155
- I don't know yet.

12:19.196 --> 12:21.574
I don't know.

12:21.615 --> 12:28.581
♪ ♪

12:28.622 --> 12:30.666
[light bulbs buzzing]

12:30.708 --> 12:37.798
♪ ♪

12:50.269 --> 12:52.772
- [sighs]

12:57.318 --> 13:04.408
♪ ♪

13:15.920 --> 13:16.962
[whoosh]

13:17.004 --> 13:20.382
[gasps]

13:20.424 --> 13:23.260
[eerie music]

13:23.302 --> 13:24.762
[shrieks]
- Oh!

13:24.804 --> 13:26.889
It's only me.
I hope I didn't scare you.

13:26.931 --> 13:30.726
- Well, yeah, a little bit.
- Please forgive me.

13:30.768 --> 13:33.312
- What are you doing here,
Mr. Swift?

13:33.354 --> 13:36.482
- Yes, well, your colleague,
um, Charlotte?

13:36.524 --> 13:38.317
She told me where you were,

13:38.359 --> 13:41.028
looking into William Zarick's
collection, and I thought,

13:41.070 --> 13:44.198
"Well, why don't we have a
little treasure hunt together?"

13:44.240 --> 13:46.200
Won't that be thrilling?

13:46.242 --> 13:48.244
[tense music]

13:48.285 --> 13:51.080
- You're trespassing,
Mr. Swift.

13:51.121 --> 13:52.665
- Perhaps.

13:52.706 --> 13:56.794
But sometimes
breaking the rules can be fun.

13:56.836 --> 14:00.589
♪ ♪

14:00.631 --> 14:02.341
- I was looking
into the inventory

14:02.383 --> 14:04.510
just in case I heard from you.

14:04.552 --> 14:06.136
- Oh, well, and here I am.

14:06.178 --> 14:08.472
- Is there anything
in particular

14:08.514 --> 14:10.099
you're looking for?

14:10.140 --> 14:12.101
- Oh, I'll know it
when I see it.

14:12.142 --> 14:19.108
♪ ♪

14:19.149 --> 14:21.735
Is, uh, this what
you're looking for?

14:21.777 --> 14:23.571
I believe you dropped it.

14:23.612 --> 14:29.410
♪ ♪

14:29.451 --> 14:31.328
- It's dead.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.455
- Oh, well, that's modern
technology for you.

14:33.497 --> 14:36.333
It lets you down
when you need it the most.

14:36.375 --> 14:43.465
♪ ♪

14:53.601 --> 14:54.935
- Find something?

14:54.977 --> 15:02.067
♪ ♪

15:09.867 --> 15:12.453
- Um...

15:12.494 --> 15:14.955
Do you mind if I--
if I keep this?

15:14.997 --> 15:17.207
It's--it's just an empty box.

15:19.168 --> 15:21.253
- I don't really think
I can let you.

15:21.295 --> 15:25.591
It's part
of the Zarick inventory.

15:25.633 --> 15:32.598
♪ ♪

15:32.640 --> 15:35.309
- Oh, dear.

15:35.351 --> 15:37.144
And there was I,

15:37.186 --> 15:40.606
thinking
we were getting on so famously.

15:43.108 --> 15:45.611
- I really must insist.

15:45.653 --> 15:46.904
[whoosh]

15:46.946 --> 15:49.698
[panting]

15:49.740 --> 15:51.492
[switch clicking]

15:51.533 --> 15:58.624
♪ ♪

16:11.637 --> 16:13.931
- History teaches us
that all civilizations

16:13.973 --> 16:15.766
eventually come to an end.

16:15.808 --> 16:18.560
But now that we're global,
that changes.

16:18.602 --> 16:19.937
We're connected.

16:19.979 --> 16:22.189
We are one civilization,

16:22.231 --> 16:25.567
vulnerable to extinction
as so many were before...

16:25.609 --> 16:28.696
[high-pitched ringing]

16:30.280 --> 16:32.491
- Yolanda, you okay?

16:32.533 --> 16:36.245
- [groans softly]
- Headaches again?

16:36.286 --> 16:37.955
- Mm-hmm.
- A disease?

16:37.997 --> 16:41.792
Or an environmental
catastrophe?

16:41.834 --> 16:44.962
- How are we gonna stop
The Shade once we find him?

16:45.004 --> 16:47.673
- Pat's working on it.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.592
- I don't wanna be
in another situation

16:50.634 --> 16:52.261
like Brainwave, Court.
- Let's take a look

16:52.302 --> 16:54.013
at some of the civilizations
that have managed...

16:54.054 --> 16:57.016
- I can't do what I did again.

16:57.057 --> 16:59.018
I won't.

16:59.059 --> 17:00.936
- Courtney? Yolanda?

17:00.978 --> 17:02.479
Care to answer?

17:04.148 --> 17:05.983
- Um...

17:06.025 --> 17:08.819
- I assume you were conferring
about the topic at hand.

17:08.861 --> 17:10.529
In 1521,

17:10.571 --> 17:14.408
why did the Aztec civilization
suddenly disappear?

17:14.450 --> 17:19.538
♪ ♪

17:19.580 --> 17:22.041
- Uh...
- Well,

17:22.082 --> 17:24.334
this conquistador named Cortés,

17:24.376 --> 17:27.671
who sounds like a total jerk,
conquered the Aztecs,

17:27.713 --> 17:29.548
so that was bad enough, right?

17:29.590 --> 17:31.842
But at the same time,
the Europeans brought over

17:31.884 --> 17:33.343
the super plague.

17:33.385 --> 17:34.678
So between them both,

17:34.720 --> 17:37.139
the Aztecs
didn't stand a chance.

17:37.181 --> 17:39.349
RIP Aztecs.

17:39.391 --> 17:42.561
- Correct, Courtney.

17:42.603 --> 17:44.271
- We'll come up with a plan

17:44.313 --> 17:47.775
that doesn't involve anything
remotely like that.

17:47.816 --> 17:49.109
I promise.

17:50.694 --> 17:52.404
- How did you know all of that?

17:53.822 --> 17:56.950
- Turns out, if you actually
read the book,

17:56.992 --> 17:59.036
history's not that hard.

18:01.914 --> 18:04.792
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

18:04.833 --> 18:06.460
- How much for those cookies?

18:06.502 --> 18:09.338
- Ooh, what's our plan here?
- You will see.

18:09.379 --> 18:10.881
- $5?

18:10.923 --> 18:13.217
- I'm not paying $5
for a box of cookies.

18:13.258 --> 18:15.719
- Look, Molly, you give us
three boxes of cookies

18:15.761 --> 18:16.762
and we walk away.

18:16.804 --> 18:18.263
- Why should I?

18:18.305 --> 18:19.264
- Because we'll crush 'em
if you don't.

18:19.306 --> 18:20.808
Now hand them over.

18:20.849 --> 18:22.851
- Yeah, and none
of that shortbread stuff!

18:22.893 --> 18:25.229
- Yeah!
- A little girl?

18:25.270 --> 18:26.688
That's worse than usual.

18:26.730 --> 18:28.357
- I'm not gonna give you
free cookies.

18:28.398 --> 18:29.900
- Oh, you're not gonna give us
free cookies?

18:29.942 --> 18:31.860
- Uh-huh, uh-huh!
- Come on, let's go!

18:31.902 --> 18:33.403
Let's go!
- Mom!

18:33.445 --> 18:34.530
- Thunderbolt,
I wish you'd make 'em stop.

18:34.571 --> 18:37.491
- You got it!

18:37.533 --> 18:39.576
[confused chatter]

18:39.618 --> 18:40.869
- That's great.

18:40.911 --> 18:44.039
Look at how freaked out
they are.

18:44.081 --> 18:45.833
[panicked chatter]

18:45.874 --> 18:47.668
- Whoa!

18:47.709 --> 18:48.794
- What is this?

18:48.836 --> 18:50.170
- O-okay, that's--that's good.

18:50.212 --> 18:51.463
You can stop now.

18:51.505 --> 18:53.966
- Well, I can't until they do.

18:54.007 --> 18:55.509
[thunder booming]

18:55.551 --> 18:57.136
- Run!

18:57.177 --> 19:00.597
[suspenseful music]

19:00.639 --> 19:07.729
♪ ♪

19:16.405 --> 19:18.323
- No, no, no. Aah!

19:24.955 --> 19:26.623
- Run!

19:28.750 --> 19:33.380
- Ah! Ah! Ah! Ah! Ah!

19:33.422 --> 19:36.842
♪ ♪

19:36.884 --> 19:38.969
- Don't worry,
we're gonna figure this out.

19:39.011 --> 19:41.138
Things are looking up
from here.

19:41.180 --> 19:47.853
♪ ♪

19:48.770 --> 19:50.939
Mike?

19:52.191 --> 19:53.525
- Guess who's the newest member

19:53.567 --> 19:56.945
of the Justice Society
of America?

19:56.987 --> 19:57.988
Me.

19:58.030 --> 19:59.323
[zapping]

19:59.364 --> 20:01.575
- You mean us! Ta-da!

20:01.617 --> 20:03.869
Pleasure to meet you.
[laughs]

20:03.911 --> 20:05.412
[car alarm blaring,
horn honking]

20:05.454 --> 20:06.455
What's going on?

20:06.496 --> 20:08.999
Sorry about the sign.

20:09.041 --> 20:10.542
Tough crowd, right?

20:14.379 --> 20:15.464
- I knew you took
the other stuff

20:15.505 --> 20:16.924
from the JSA headquarters,

20:16.965 --> 20:18.300
but you didn't tell me
you took the pen.

20:18.342 --> 20:19.384
- I forgot about it!
- Okay, Court,

20:19.426 --> 20:20.636
I told you it was dangerous.

20:20.677 --> 20:22.346
Somebody could
have been killed.

20:22.387 --> 20:23.597
- Well, you should've told me
everything about it

20:23.639 --> 20:24.890
in the first place.

20:24.932 --> 20:28.060
You know, been specific.

20:28.101 --> 20:30.479
- You gotta be real specific
with the wishing,

20:30.520 --> 20:32.564
let me tell you, pal.
- No, Mike. No more wishes.

20:32.606 --> 20:37.027
- But, Mr. Dugan, if this genie
really grants wishes,

20:37.069 --> 20:39.196
maybe he could fix the goggles?

20:39.238 --> 20:41.281
- Or find The Shade?
- And stop him.

20:41.323 --> 20:43.492
- Trust me, he'd just
cause more trouble.

20:43.533 --> 20:44.993
- Me?

20:45.035 --> 20:47.162
- No, not you, Mike,
The Thunderbolt.

20:47.204 --> 20:50.666
He's not exactly a living
monkey's paw, but he's close.

20:50.707 --> 20:52.876
[crackling tone]

20:52.918 --> 20:54.586
- I think he can hear you.

20:54.628 --> 20:57.214
Also, what's this got
to do with monkeys?

20:57.256 --> 20:58.799
- Okay, give me the pen.

20:58.840 --> 21:00.425
- No.
- Now!

21:00.467 --> 21:01.760
- You're saying
I can't handle it.

21:01.802 --> 21:03.262
- Nobody can.

21:03.303 --> 21:05.430
I'm sorry, all right, Mike?
I really am.

21:05.472 --> 21:08.100
It's just that The Thunderbolt,
he's too unpredictable.

21:17.276 --> 21:19.528
- [laughs]

21:19.569 --> 21:20.904
- [clears throat] Give me that.

21:22.948 --> 21:24.324
Thank you.

21:24.366 --> 21:26.827
Hey!
- [laughs]

21:26.868 --> 21:28.412
- Ah!

21:29.913 --> 21:32.040
Guess he likes hanging
with the boss.

21:32.082 --> 21:33.750
- Call him out here right now.

21:33.792 --> 21:35.794
I want to speak
to The Thunderbolt alone.

21:35.836 --> 21:38.797
[dramatic music]

21:38.839 --> 21:41.091
♪ ♪

21:41.133 --> 21:42.509
- Sowkewl.

21:42.551 --> 21:44.845
[whooshing]

21:44.886 --> 21:47.973
[thunder booming]

21:49.266 --> 21:51.810
- Still zipping around, I see.

21:52.811 --> 21:55.147
- I can't believe
you built this!

21:55.188 --> 21:57.816
If Starman had seen it,
I'm sure he would have

21:57.858 --> 22:01.820
promoted you from sidekick
to, like, senior sidekick

22:01.862 --> 22:04.448
or, you know,
he would have been happy!

22:04.489 --> 22:06.325
- Yeah, well, it's not a toy.

22:06.366 --> 22:08.952
- So there's
a new JSA now, huh?

22:08.994 --> 22:11.621
- Yeah, but you know
how dangerous this life can be,

22:11.663 --> 22:15.125
and even with power like yours,

22:15.167 --> 22:16.626
Johnny died.

22:17.169 --> 22:21.506
- I remember his smile
when he made that last wish

22:21.548 --> 22:25.052
and then...he was gone.

22:25.093 --> 22:27.512
- Yeah, so what was
his last wish?

22:27.554 --> 22:30.515
- That I'd find a new friend.

22:30.557 --> 22:32.726
- Mike? Why him?

22:32.768 --> 22:34.728
- You know how it works.

22:34.770 --> 22:38.190
I can only pick someone like me
to be partners with.

22:38.231 --> 22:42.986
Someone who feels completely
and utterly alone.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.406
- That's really how he feels?

22:46.448 --> 22:49.117
- Right now? Yeah.

22:49.159 --> 22:54.414
♪ ♪

22:54.456 --> 22:55.540
- Okay.

22:55.582 --> 23:02.672
♪ ♪

23:08.637 --> 23:10.472
- Hey.

23:10.514 --> 23:11.681
So did you guys
have a vote yet?

23:11.723 --> 23:13.016
Am I in the JSA,
or do I have

23:13.058 --> 23:14.351
to go through
some hazing first?

23:14.393 --> 23:18.313
- There's no hazing.
- Oh. Great.

23:18.355 --> 23:20.065
So I'm in, right?

23:21.817 --> 23:23.443
- It's not up to me.

23:23.485 --> 23:26.113
- Yeah, it is.
You're, like, the JSA's leader.

23:26.154 --> 23:27.823
- But Pat's your dad.

23:27.864 --> 23:30.033
That's veto power
I can't overrule.

23:30.075 --> 23:31.618
- He told you no too.

23:31.660 --> 23:33.870
Come on, Court, think about it.

23:33.912 --> 23:36.373
All the bad guys
we'll be able to take down.

23:36.415 --> 23:38.291
All the people
we'll be able to save.

23:38.333 --> 23:40.377
You and me together,
brother and sister!

23:40.419 --> 23:42.796
- That sounds great,
really, but--

23:42.838 --> 23:44.548
- The Thunderbolt picked me.

23:44.589 --> 23:46.716
So I'm like you.

23:46.758 --> 23:47.968
I was meant to be a superhero.

23:48.009 --> 23:50.220
It's my destiny.

23:50.262 --> 23:53.932
Please, help me try?

23:53.974 --> 23:58.687
♪ ♪

23:58.728 --> 24:00.397
- [chuckles]

24:00.439 --> 24:06.361
♪ ♪

24:06.403 --> 24:08.280
- Pat,
we've come to a decision.

24:08.321 --> 24:10.782
- Hey, this is not
a group discussion, okay?

24:10.824 --> 24:13.034
- But Mike deserves
to be in the JSA.

24:13.076 --> 24:15.245
- We voted.
- Just call me Mikey Thunder.

24:15.287 --> 24:17.581
- Let me handle this.

24:17.622 --> 24:19.833
Also, that's terrible.

24:19.875 --> 24:22.502
Mike and The Thunderbolt
could find The Shade for us.

24:22.544 --> 24:24.087
- We don't have
any leads on him, Pat.

24:24.129 --> 24:25.922
- And the goggles
haven't found him.

24:25.964 --> 24:29.885
- The Thunderbolt,
it's dangerous, Beth, okay?

24:29.926 --> 24:31.428
- You didn't want me to use
the Cosmic Staff

24:31.470 --> 24:33.472
for the same reason.
- You didn't want

24:33.513 --> 24:34.848
any of us suiting up
at first.

24:34.890 --> 24:37.517
- But together
we stopped the ISA.

24:37.559 --> 24:39.227
And Mike helped.

24:39.269 --> 24:40.979
He stopped Icicle,
if you remember.

24:41.021 --> 24:42.981
- Yeah, I try to not
think about it.

24:43.023 --> 24:46.276
- We need to find The Shade,
and Mike and The Thunderbolt

24:46.318 --> 24:48.612
are our best chance
of doing that right now.

24:48.653 --> 24:50.780
- She rests my case.

24:51.948 --> 24:54.201
- [clears throat]

24:54.242 --> 24:57.746
Okay, you can help us
locate The Shade.

24:57.787 --> 25:00.081
That's it. Deal?

25:00.123 --> 25:02.083
- My man.

25:02.125 --> 25:05.212
- All right, knowing
how these wishes can backfire,

25:05.253 --> 25:07.672
we gotta come up with one
that's bulletproof

25:07.714 --> 25:09.299
and I need all of your help.

25:09.341 --> 25:15.222
[Peter Gabriel's "Big Time"]

25:15.263 --> 25:17.599
- ♪ I'm on my way,
I'm making it ♪

25:17.641 --> 25:20.227
- No!

25:20.268 --> 25:22.395
[indistinct chatter]
Okay, but--

25:22.437 --> 25:25.398
- ♪ I've got to make it show,
yeah ♪

25:25.440 --> 25:26.942
♪ ♪

25:26.983 --> 25:30.654
- Yes!
- Okay, great, great, great.

25:30.695 --> 25:32.405
- ♪ Big time ♪

25:32.447 --> 25:35.116
- ♪ I'm on my way,
I'm making it ♪

25:35.158 --> 25:38.995
- ♪ Big time ♪
- ♪ Oh, yes ♪

25:39.037 --> 25:40.705
- ♪ Big time ♪

25:40.747 --> 25:43.416
- ♪ I've got to make it show,
yeah ♪

25:43.458 --> 25:45.710
- ♪ Big time ♪

25:45.752 --> 25:47.295
♪ Big time ♪

25:47.337 --> 25:48.880
♪ ♪

25:48.922 --> 25:50.966
- ♪ Big, big, big, big ♪

25:51.007 --> 25:53.385
♪ Big, big,
big, big ♪

25:53.426 --> 25:55.345
♪ Big, big, big, big ♪

25:55.387 --> 25:57.639
♪ Big, big, big ♪

25:59.099 --> 26:01.184
- So...

26:01.226 --> 26:03.061
in conclusion,

26:03.103 --> 26:06.731
show us the location
of "The Shade,"

26:06.773 --> 26:09.693
not to be confused
with a lamp or window shade,

26:09.734 --> 26:11.027
but the last known member

26:11.069 --> 26:13.530
of the Injustice Society
of America,

26:13.572 --> 26:15.824
hiding somewhere
in Blue Valley, Nebraska,

26:15.865 --> 26:19.160
68060, USA.

26:20.537 --> 26:21.788
[shimmering tone]

26:21.830 --> 26:24.791
[dramatic music]

26:24.833 --> 26:29.379
♪ ♪

26:29.421 --> 26:31.089
- Where is he?

26:33.258 --> 26:35.427
- That's William Zarick's
old house.

26:35.468 --> 26:38.013
- That's The Wizard, right?
- Yeah.

26:38.054 --> 26:41.266
- Hey, you did it, Mike!
- Yeah, you did good.

26:41.308 --> 26:42.642
- Thanks, Dad. Let's go!

26:42.684 --> 26:44.311
- Whoa! Whoa!

26:44.352 --> 26:46.605
You're staying here.
- What?

26:46.646 --> 26:48.148
- Yeah, that was the deal,
remember?

26:48.189 --> 26:49.608
You agreed to it.

26:49.649 --> 26:51.443
And it's safer that way
for everyone.

26:51.484 --> 26:52.902
- No, no, no, no, no.

26:52.944 --> 26:54.571
Come on, man.
Don't bench me now. I--

26:54.613 --> 26:57.449
- I'm sorry, Mike,
that's just the way it is.

26:57.490 --> 27:00.410
- Mike, you really did help us.

27:00.452 --> 27:03.580
- Hey, you guard the Pit Stop.

27:03.622 --> 27:05.665
That's an important job, right?

27:05.707 --> 27:07.250
[door opens]

27:07.292 --> 27:09.628
There's some, uh, pizza bites,
string cheese,

27:09.669 --> 27:12.213
and some of those
juice boxes you like.

27:12.255 --> 27:15.842
♪ ♪

27:15.884 --> 27:18.470
- Mikey Thunder,

27:18.511 --> 27:20.388
riding the pine.

27:20.430 --> 27:23.433
♪ ♪

27:28.396 --> 27:29.814
- Okay, so let's go over this
one more time.

27:29.856 --> 27:31.441
what's the plan?
- Nothing fancy, Barb.

27:31.483 --> 27:33.652
We go in, we locate The Shade.

27:33.693 --> 27:35.487
Rick and Yolanda,
they restrain him

27:35.528 --> 27:37.656
until Courtney
gets there with the Staff

27:37.697 --> 27:40.533
and renders him unconscious,
just like Sylvester did.

27:40.575 --> 27:42.369
- Okay. And then?

27:42.410 --> 27:46.039
- Beth's located a suitable
device to negate his powers

27:46.081 --> 27:48.291
until we can deliver him
to the proper authorities.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.251
- Who are
the proper authorities?

27:50.293 --> 27:51.878
And what device?

27:53.296 --> 27:54.714
- Tanning bed, actually,

27:54.756 --> 27:56.591
your old one
that's out in the garage.

27:56.633 --> 27:58.426
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

27:58.468 --> 28:00.595
- What's Mike gonna do?
- He'll be down at the Pit Stop

28:00.637 --> 28:02.305
waiting for the play-by-play.

28:02.347 --> 28:03.807
It's gonna be fine.
Don't worry about us.

28:03.848 --> 28:06.267
I'll call up and give you
a little heads-up.

28:06.309 --> 28:08.395
- Okay.

28:10.980 --> 28:14.693
[heroic music]

28:14.734 --> 28:16.319
- Approved?
- Yeah.

28:16.361 --> 28:20.407
Um, your mother thinks
the plan is acceptable.

28:20.448 --> 28:23.451
- Then let's go get this jerk.
- For Chuck.

28:25.161 --> 28:27.789
- We'll restrain him,
then imprison him.

28:27.831 --> 28:32.585
♪ ♪

28:32.627 --> 28:36.506
- With--with caution, right?
Okay?

28:36.548 --> 28:39.509
[dramatic music]

28:39.551 --> 28:46.015
♪ ♪

29:08.663 --> 29:10.874
- [sighs]

29:13.835 --> 29:20.925
♪ ♪

29:42.405 --> 29:44.616
[dark music]

29:44.657 --> 29:46.367
- Okay, so what's the deal?

29:46.409 --> 29:48.411
- Blue Valley declared this
a historic home

29:48.453 --> 29:50.955
after the Zaricks...departed.

29:53.333 --> 29:57.212
- It'll be historic once
I get my hands on The Shade.

29:57.253 --> 30:00.340
- What does that even mean?
- I don't know. I'm amped.

30:00.381 --> 30:01.674
- Hey, quiet!

30:01.716 --> 30:04.260
Very quiet, all right?

30:04.302 --> 30:06.387
[zapping]

30:06.429 --> 30:13.520
♪ ♪

30:35.917 --> 30:38.002
[whooshing]

30:38.044 --> 30:42.423
♪ ♪

30:42.465 --> 30:44.551
- Oh, my.

30:44.592 --> 30:46.302
Quite the assembly.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.471
I hope I have enough biscuits.

30:48.513 --> 30:50.849
Come, come. Do sit down.

30:50.890 --> 30:53.476
The tea is nicely steeped.

30:53.518 --> 30:56.354
It's perfect, in fact,
if I say so myself.

30:56.396 --> 30:58.940
- We're not here for teatime,
Shade.

30:58.982 --> 31:00.817
What are you doing
in Blue Valley?

31:00.859 --> 31:02.986
- Pat Dugan.

31:03.027 --> 31:06.114
It took me a moment
to place the name in the diner.

31:06.155 --> 31:08.992
- By the way, I knew that was
a 1967 Jag, right?

31:09.033 --> 31:10.285
You know that?

31:10.326 --> 31:12.161
- Well, of course I do,
Stripesy.

31:13.246 --> 31:15.248
Oh, I see.

31:15.290 --> 31:20.086
Same sidekick,
different Star-Spangled Kid.

31:20.128 --> 31:21.504
- Stargirl.

31:21.546 --> 31:23.798
- Oh, absolutely.

31:23.840 --> 31:25.967
Now, please sit.

31:26.009 --> 31:27.969
[Staff warbling]

31:28.011 --> 31:30.680
We could do it the other way,
I suppose,

31:30.722 --> 31:34.267
all bother and perspiration,

31:34.309 --> 31:37.478
or we could try
the more genteel approach.

31:37.520 --> 31:39.147
- You murdered Dr. Mid-Nite.

31:39.188 --> 31:41.065
You don't deserve
the genteel approach!

31:41.107 --> 31:42.942
- My dear young lady--

31:42.984 --> 31:45.904
and I mean this
in the nicest possible way--

31:45.945 --> 31:48.448
you don't know
what you're talking about.

31:49.782 --> 31:52.785
Now, sit.

31:52.827 --> 31:55.538
I implore you.

31:55.580 --> 31:57.749
[tense music]

31:57.790 --> 32:00.710
- All right, kids,
let's go ahead and have a seat.

32:00.752 --> 32:02.253
- Wonderful.

32:02.295 --> 32:03.838
- Thank you.

32:03.880 --> 32:06.549
Try anything,
and I'll see how many teacups

32:06.591 --> 32:08.968
I can shove down your throat.

32:09.010 --> 32:12.180
- Don't you teach these
children any manners, Stripesy?

32:12.221 --> 32:15.642
- So I'm just gonna ask you
again, Shade,

32:15.683 --> 32:17.185
why are you here?

32:17.226 --> 32:18.853
- We won't let you
hurt our town.

32:18.895 --> 32:20.563
- And whyever would I do that?

32:20.605 --> 32:23.524
- Because you were a member
of the Injustice Society.

32:23.566 --> 32:26.277
- Our interests aligned
for a moment,

32:26.319 --> 32:29.572
but birds of a feather
we were not.

32:29.614 --> 32:32.033
Jordan Mahkent
and his merry band

32:32.075 --> 32:33.493
were no friends of mine.

32:33.534 --> 32:35.328
Icicle was a lunatic.

32:35.370 --> 32:36.788
If there's one thing worse

32:36.829 --> 32:38.122
than a man
who wants to rule the world,

32:38.164 --> 32:41.376
it's a man
who wants to save it.

32:41.417 --> 32:45.171
Though seeing the way
your generation's going,

32:45.213 --> 32:47.882
I expect you'll
end humanity for good.

32:47.924 --> 32:49.550
- Okay, just because
you gave up

32:49.592 --> 32:51.010
and only looked out
for yourself

32:51.052 --> 32:53.137
doesn't mean
we're ever going to.

32:53.179 --> 32:55.139
We're never gonna stop fighting
to protect the world

32:55.181 --> 32:56.849
from people like you.

32:57.725 --> 32:59.227
- Just to reassure you,

32:59.268 --> 33:02.522
I have no dark design
on Blue Valley.

33:02.563 --> 33:04.440
Stay out of my way,

33:04.482 --> 33:06.693
and I'll be gone
before you know it.

33:06.734 --> 33:09.654
- Why are you here?

33:09.696 --> 33:11.990
- Young lady,
I'm not being coy.

33:13.700 --> 33:16.202
It's just better
that none of you know.

33:18.079 --> 33:20.790
Now, please, try the tea.

33:20.832 --> 33:24.460
♪ ♪

33:24.502 --> 33:26.170
- Thunderbolt,

33:26.212 --> 33:28.131
I wish you'd zap the villain
known as "The Shade,"

33:28.172 --> 33:30.383
not to be confused with a lamp
or window shade.

33:30.425 --> 33:32.885
- As you wish, my friend.

33:32.927 --> 33:36.931
Whoo-whee!

33:36.973 --> 33:39.976
Ow! Ooh!

33:40.018 --> 33:42.270
Ow! Aah!

33:43.813 --> 33:44.856
- Mike!

33:44.897 --> 33:46.441
Mike, Mike!

33:46.482 --> 33:48.901
[Staff warbles]
- [grunts]

33:50.361 --> 33:52.155
- [grunting]

33:52.196 --> 33:53.906
- [groans]

33:53.948 --> 34:01.039
♪ ♪

34:07.879 --> 34:11.424
[screeching]

34:11.466 --> 34:14.427
[tense music]

34:14.469 --> 34:19.724
♪ ♪

34:19.766 --> 34:23.394
- I'll say it
for the last time.

34:23.436 --> 34:27.023
Stay out of my way!

34:27.065 --> 34:34.155
♪ ♪

34:35.782 --> 34:37.366
- [grunting]

34:37.408 --> 34:43.664
♪ ♪

34:43.706 --> 34:45.833
- You okay?
- Yeah.

34:45.875 --> 34:48.920
♪ ♪

34:59.472 --> 35:02.308
- Hey, Mike.

35:02.350 --> 35:03.976
You okay?

35:06.646 --> 35:09.232
- No.

35:09.273 --> 35:10.942
No, not really.

35:13.194 --> 35:14.862
I thought I could help
you guys,

35:14.904 --> 35:16.572
but, you know, I blew it.

35:21.994 --> 35:25.456
- Do you ever feel bad
about what happened?

35:25.498 --> 35:28.543
You know, with Icicle and all?

35:31.420 --> 35:33.214
- Yeah, about that.

35:34.632 --> 35:37.802
Truth is, I was hauling ass,
you know?

35:37.844 --> 35:42.181
Look up, Icicle's in the middle
of the road icing up, and bam!

35:44.350 --> 35:46.102
He was ice cubes
before I even knew it.

35:46.144 --> 35:48.104
- It was an accident?

35:50.398 --> 35:52.567
- Well, yeah.

35:52.608 --> 35:54.193
Yeah, I guess it was.

35:55.903 --> 35:57.905
I'm no hero.

36:01.117 --> 36:03.244
- We looked for him everywhere.

36:03.286 --> 36:04.829
He's gone.

36:13.462 --> 36:15.590
- Okay...

36:15.631 --> 36:17.508
I know I should've
listened, but--

36:17.550 --> 36:18.926
- You didn't!

36:18.968 --> 36:20.261
- I didn't either
in the beginning.

36:20.303 --> 36:21.846
- Courtney.

36:21.888 --> 36:24.599
- This is the beginning
for Mike, Mom,

36:24.640 --> 36:26.517
with The Thunderbolt.

36:26.559 --> 36:30.479
Even if Mike hadn't shown up,
The Shade was way ahead of us.

36:30.521 --> 36:32.064
You saw, Pat.

36:32.106 --> 36:34.233
- No.

36:34.275 --> 36:35.818
No, I screwed up.

36:38.529 --> 36:41.324
Thought this pen
was my ticket into the JSA,

36:41.365 --> 36:44.118
but now I kind of just wish
it was in better hands.

36:44.160 --> 36:46.871
- No!
- Thunderbolt?

36:46.913 --> 36:49.874
[dramatic music]

36:49.916 --> 36:56.881
♪ ♪

36:56.923 --> 37:00.009
[video game blipping]

37:05.306 --> 37:08.267
- Jakeem, Mom wants you
to take out the trash.

37:08.309 --> 37:10.102
- But I got a high score.

37:10.144 --> 37:12.063
- On your one-player game?

37:12.104 --> 37:15.024
Get some friends that aren't
Pac-Man and Luigi.

37:15.066 --> 37:18.694
- Move your butt, Jakeem,
before I call your father!

37:18.736 --> 37:20.655
- You know what Dad's
gonna say--

37:20.696 --> 37:24.492
what everyone does:
you're a loser!

37:30.373 --> 37:34.043
- [sighs] I am a loser.

37:34.085 --> 37:37.255
- Yoo-hoo!

37:37.296 --> 37:38.798
- What?

37:38.839 --> 37:42.051
[exciting music]

37:42.093 --> 37:44.095
Where did you come from?

37:44.136 --> 37:46.472
- [laughs]

37:46.514 --> 37:48.724
♪ ♪

37:48.766 --> 37:51.727
[soft music]

37:51.769 --> 37:54.397
♪ ♪

37:54.438 --> 37:56.774
- Is Mike okay?
- He's okay.

37:56.816 --> 37:58.943
Court's upstairs with him.

38:00.778 --> 38:03.489
You know...

38:03.531 --> 38:07.618
The Thunderbolt
told me that he chose Mike

38:07.660 --> 38:10.121
because Mike felt so alone.

38:12.206 --> 38:15.167
- I mean, that's on all of us
if it's true.

38:15.209 --> 38:18.462
- Yeah, I mean,

38:18.504 --> 38:20.965
the kid, he just wants to be
a part of the team,

38:21.007 --> 38:22.133
and I get it.

38:22.174 --> 38:24.427
- He is, though, pen or no pen.

38:24.468 --> 38:26.804
I mean, we both are,

38:26.846 --> 38:30.016
even though we don't have
costumes and code names.

38:32.226 --> 38:34.937
I think I found something.

38:34.979 --> 38:37.064
- What?
- Well, I was looking through

38:37.106 --> 38:39.150
Zarick's inventory logs,

38:39.191 --> 38:42.737
and the empty box Swift took,

38:42.778 --> 38:44.155
it contained a diamond.

38:44.196 --> 38:46.198
[tense music]

38:46.240 --> 38:47.825
- A diamond?
- Yeah.

38:47.867 --> 38:49.660
It said "costume jewelry"
on it.

38:49.702 --> 38:54.206
Maybe a magic prop.
It was black.

38:54.248 --> 38:57.084
- It was no prop, Barb.

38:57.126 --> 38:59.086
That's the black diamond.

39:00.671 --> 39:02.423
- What's the black diamond?

39:03.674 --> 39:06.886
- It's something
very, very bad.

39:06.927 --> 39:09.347
♪ ♪

39:09.388 --> 39:11.265
[computer blipping]

39:11.307 --> 39:14.101
- Ugh!

39:14.143 --> 39:17.605
[sighs] It's still not working!

39:17.646 --> 39:19.273
- It's okay.

39:19.315 --> 39:20.983
We'll get Chuck back.

39:21.025 --> 39:22.318
- No.

39:22.360 --> 39:24.278
It's useless, Rick.

39:24.320 --> 39:26.697
I'm never getting Chuck back,

39:26.739 --> 39:28.657
and we lost
Dr. Mid-Nite's killer.

39:28.699 --> 39:30.701
Everything's falling apart!

39:32.578 --> 39:35.706
- What's going on?

39:35.748 --> 39:37.416
Beth?

39:40.211 --> 39:42.755
Hey, you can--you can
talk to me.

39:44.840 --> 39:47.176
Pretend I'm Chuck.

39:59.855 --> 40:02.525
- I think my parents
might be getting a divorce.

40:04.068 --> 40:05.903
- What?

40:05.945 --> 40:07.780
Did they say something?

40:07.822 --> 40:09.615
- No.

40:09.657 --> 40:12.410
I found some papers.
- Okay.

40:12.451 --> 40:15.788
Well, papers are just papers.

40:15.830 --> 40:17.915
You should talk to them.

40:24.422 --> 40:27.258
I would talk to mine,
if I could.

40:34.515 --> 40:35.975
[static crackles]

40:36.016 --> 40:38.102
- Hello?
- Chuck!

40:38.144 --> 40:40.563
Chuck?

40:40.604 --> 40:41.981
Chuck!

40:42.022 --> 40:43.274
Chuck, I can hear you!

40:43.315 --> 40:45.359
It's me! It's Beth!

40:45.401 --> 40:46.944
- You have to listen.

40:46.986 --> 40:48.654
Whoever you are,
you need to know...

40:48.696 --> 40:51.198
- What?
- You're in danger.

40:51.240 --> 40:52.992
Eclipso--

40:53.033 --> 40:54.368
- Chuck?

40:54.410 --> 40:56.078
- What was it?
What did Chuck say?

40:56.120 --> 41:01.792
♪ ♪

41:01.834 --> 41:04.044
- He said we're in danger.

41:05.713 --> 41:08.466
He said Eclipso is here.

41:08.507 --> 41:15.598
♪ ♪

41:40.498 --> 41:43.000
- He's gonna kill
those children.

41:49.048 --> 41:52.009
[dramatic music]

41:52.051 --> 41:59.141
♪ ♪

42:08.442 --> 42:10.027
- Greg, move your head.
